    "It is our aim to improve precision, thereby refining the models to yield more discerning predictions and achieve a more favorable balance between the two metrics.",
    "This pursuit aligns with the findings of Chen et al., 45 who report binary F1 scores around 50%, in stark contrast to AUC scores of over 90%.",
    "Such a significant gap highlights a likely skewed distribution within their dataset, potentially obfuscating the true efficacy of their model.",
    "This imbalance accentuates the importance of employing weighted metrics, such as the weighted F1 score, to gain a more comprehensive understanding of a model's performance in imbalanced datasets.",
    "Nevertheless, for consistency with established benchmarks, we opted to report binary F1 scores."
